body:
i can't seem to share with anyone, even if they are in the same group, when the "allow users to only share with users in their groups" is checked.  when i uncheck this, i can share with anyone, but if this is checked no sharing is possible.

to repeat:
create users 1, 2 and 3.  make them a member of group users.
make sure the "allow users to only share with users in their groups" is checked in the admin panel
log out, and back in as user 1.
try to share a folder with other users on the system - no other users show up, even though users 2 and 3 are there and part of the same group.
log back in as admin
switch the "allow users to only share with users in their groups" to "allow users to share with anyone".  
now log back in as user 1 and share with users, or user 1 and 2

centos 6.2, mysql, owncloud 5.0.0 alpha1

